n that - on the Christmas cav we played with the new toys to best of my recollection and just waited for the wonderful Christmas dinner and the tea. Pork by the way was always for Christmas dinner. That was deemed very - very high. Pork.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7634190 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14951568\charrsid19052 Any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11674240 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14951568\charrsid19052 Well only a mouth organ and a comb and tissue paper. That's the only -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7634190 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14951568\charrsid19052 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11674240 AR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14951568\charrsid19052 Yes. We all sang, and mother had a big repertoire of songs which we learned too. Scottish and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
